  "notes": [
    "Sprint 97 progresses the management / production aspect by adding managed environments and remote-readonly readiness while remaining pre-deployment.",
    "Governance preflight is required before any work-producing run: export SPRINT_CODE=S97, export PS_WORK_PRODUCING=1, then make -C ps-dev governance-lock-check.",
    "project_root vs bridge_root separation remains mandatory: governed evidence under project_root, scratch/caches/logs under bridge_root.",
    "Managed environments are governed by .planestack/governance/operate/environments.json; auth profiles are governed by .planestack/governance/operate/auth-profiles.json.",
    "Remote mode is read-only only in Sprint 97. No deployments, remote writeback, or mutable production actions are allowed.",
    "Operate remains the execution cockpit; Chronicle remains the reporting substrate. No duplicate reporting engine may be introduced.",
    "Authenticated capture is limited to allowlisted targets with vaulted auth-profile references and SSRF blocking.",
    "No anonymous access is allowed; external access remains invite-only and authenticated.",
    "MFA status surfaces must cover privileged and external users with explainable blocked states.",
    "Blank or ambiguous UI states are forbidden on managed-environment surfaces. Explicit states include healthy, at_risk, breached, insufficient_data, blocked, auth_failed, unreachable, and disabled.",
    "All new evidence artifacts reuse the integrity rule: sha256 of canonical JSON excluding generated_at and integrity.",
    "sprint97-validate, contract-test-docker, and e2e-gate are all blocking and independent."
  ],
